EMAIL ETIQUETTE

----------------------------------------

Introduction

Email is an important mode of communication in academic and professional environments. Writing proper emails helps in creating a good impression and ensures clear communication.

----------------------------------------

Sample Email 1 (Extension Request)

Subject: Request for Assignment Deadline Extension  

Respected Sir/Ma’am,  

I hope you are doing well. I am writing to request an extension for the assignment submission due to some personal reasons. I assure you that I will complete and submit the assignment as soon as possible.  

Kindly grant me an extension. I will be very thankful to you.  

Thanking you.  

Yours sincerely,  
Hrithik Roshan  

----------------------------------------

Sample Email 2 (Internship Application)

Subject: Application for Internship Opportunity  

Respected Sir/Ma’am,  

I am a first-year B.Tech CSE student at VIT Bhopal University. I am writing to express my interest in applying for an internship opportunity in your organization.  

I am eager to learn and enhance my skills in programming and technology. I would be grateful if you consider my application.  

Thank you for your time and consideration.  

Yours sincerely,  
Hrithik Roshan  

----------------------------------------

Email Etiquette Checklist

• Use a clear and relevant subject line  
• Start with a proper greeting  
• Keep the message short and clear  
• Use polite and professional language  
• Avoid grammatical mistakes  
• End with a proper closing  

----------------------------------------

Conclusion

Proper email etiquette is important for effective communication. It helps in maintaining professionalism and creating a positive impression.
